    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "Supplementary Note 1. Assessment of selec5on on other variants in the IFNL locus A classical problem in popula0on gene0cs is the iden0fica0on of the par0cular gene0c variant responsible for selec0on signals. The rs368234815 TT allele has a strong phenotypic effect by trunca0ng IFNL4, but we cannot per se rule out that another allele on the TT haplotype drives the selec0ve signature. As Figure 3a --c and Supplementary Figure 2 show there are other variants with comparable F ST or XP--EHH values. The two variants ini0ally described as being associated with HCV clearance are rs12979860 [1,2] and rs8099917 [3] . Both variants show weaker combined selec0on signals than the TT allele (Supplementary Fig. 2) . This is in line with the unclear func0onal effects of these variants [4--8] and their weaker associa0on with HCV clearance compared to rs368234815 in several popula0ons [9--11]. Thus, rs12979860 and rs8099917 are much weaker candidates to be the target of natural selec0on.",
